HEADWORD: Dilaniate
<hw>Di*la"ni*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dilaniatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>dilaniare</ets> to dilacerate;
<ets>di- = dis-</ets> + <ets>laniare</ets> to tear to pieces.]</ety>
<def>To rend in pieces; to tear.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

